  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dca\u0dbb\u0ddd \u0d9c\u0dd1\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0db8 \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0d9a \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dd4\u0db4\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dc5\u0dd2\u0db6\u0db3\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Litro Gas Lanka Company explains about employee salaries",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Muditha Peiris, President / Chief Executive Officer of the company, explains the facts regarding the false information that has been published in the country about the salary structure of the staff of Litro Gas Lanka Company, the national LP gas supplier of Sri Lanka, which made a profit of more than 500 million rupees before the year 2019.",
        "The existence of the company has been severely affected due to the increase in global LP gas prices and the high exchange rate of LP gas imports, but not increasing the price of LP gas in Sri Lanka. Mr. Peiris says that Litro Gas Lanka Company, which continued to be a strong company with great growth, has now become a loss-making company due to providing cost benefits to customers.",
        "He points out that Litro Gas Lanka, a wholly-owned subsidiary of the Sri Lanka Insurance Corporation, has been a strength of the country by contributing greatly to the country's economy since its inception. He also says.",
        "Employs less than 200 employees and spends less than 2% of total annual turnover on salaries. Most of the employees here have been working for more than 20 years from Lanka Gas Company and International Shell Gas Company.",
        "\"Our staff consists of many professionals with global expertise and local experience in the energy sector, and our employees are not paid pensions, tax-free incentives or other benefits provided to government employees from the state treasury,\" Mr. Peiris points out.",
        "The salary structure of Litro Gas Lanka Company is governed by the Companies Act No. 07 of 2007 and it is regulated to be similar to other public enterprises. Therefore, he reiterates that false information spread in social media will never happen in our company.",
        "The company says that such baseless allegations are made with the aim of adversely affecting the trust of customers towards the company. Therefore, the company strongly denies the accusations and reiterates that this was a deliberate act aimed at damaging the reputation of Litro Gas Lanka as the leading LP gas supplier in the country over the years."
      ],
